Generally, Facebook has less likelihood for DP although there’s still a reasonable chance a DP question will be asked (or it can be solved with DP). There’s a large group of people at Facebook that think DP is not a good measure of an engineer’s problem-solving ability which is why it’s slightly less frequency. This is different than Google and Palantir where DP is much more common. However, we've noticed a trend that as people are getting better at technical interviews DP continuously increasing in frequency even at Facebook.

Ninja Interviews (Two formats)

Ninja interviews are interviews focused on data structures and algorithms. All phone screens for software engineers are ninja interviews. For new grads on onsite, one interview will be a Jedi interview. Ping Derrick when you get to this stage for more info.

There are usually two types of interview formats on “Ninja” interviews. Both formats will have 40 minutes to code and 5 minutes 

Two 20 minute questions (Leetcode Medium)

The interviewer will try to get through two questions in 40 minutes. See the questions above that have “20 minutes” attached to them

One 40 minute question (Leetcode Hard)

The interviewer will ask a leetcode hard question and you’ll have 40 minutes to solve the question. Sometimes the question will start off easier and the interviewer will make it a leetcode hard by adding an additional constraint

Phone screen details

A phone screen will always be a ninja interview. Don’t worry about behavioral questions. They’ll want to maximize the time for you to code. Just be prepped for “Why Facebook” and asking good questions below.

